{"word":"G2176 - εὐώνυμος - euṓnymos - yoo-o'-noo-mos - Left","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐώνυμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">euṓnymos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">yoo-o'-noo-mos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Left</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"இடது - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"left"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G2095 - εὖ - eû - yoo/2095\">G2095</a> and <a href=\"#/G3686 - ὄνομα - ónoma - on'-om-ah/3686\">G3686</a>; properly <i>well named</i> (<i>good omened</i>), that is, the <i>left</i> (which was the <i>lucky</i> side among the pagan Greeks); neuter as adverb <i>at the left</i> hand: - (on the) left.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}